## Recommended Detection Toolchain

| Tool | Purpose | Usage |
|------|---------|-------|
| `cargo check` | Fast compilation check for ownership, borrowing, and type errors | Run on every save; catches Categories 1-2, 5 |
| `cargo clippy -D warnings` | Lint for idiomatic issues, performance, and correctness | Run in CI; catches Categories 4-7 |
| `clippy::unwrap_used` | Deny all `.unwrap()` calls | Add to `clippy.toml` or `#![deny()]`; catches Category 4 |
| `cargo fmt` | Enforce consistent formatting | Run in CI as a gate; catches Category 12 formatting issues |
| `cargo-geiger` | Count and audit `unsafe` usage | Run periodically; catches Category 3 |
| `cargo audit` | Check dependencies for known vulnerabilities | Run in CI; catches Category 9 |
| `cargo bench` + flamegraph | Profile performance and identify hot paths | Run before merging perf-sensitive code; catches Categories 7, 10 |
| `proptest` | Property-based testing for boundary conditions | Add to test suite; catches Category 10 |
| `cargo miri test` | Detect undefined behavior in unsafe code | Run in CI (nightly only); catches Category 3 |

